model_explanation: S1, with prosodic focus on "BILL," means that Sam didn't give bananas to anyone other than Bill. However, S2 introduces that Sam also gave Bill grapes, which doesn’t contradict the exclusive nature of S1's focus. Instead, it contradicts the implication that Bill only received bananas. Hence, S2 contradicts the inferred exclusivity introduced by S1.
S1, with prosodic focus on "MARY," means that Sam didn't give apples to anyone other than Mary. S2 directly contradicts this by stating that Sam also gave apples to Ellen.
S1, with prosodic focus on "SUE," implies that Sue was the only recipient of apples. S2 contradicts this by stating that Tom also received apples.

S1, with prosodic focus on "BILL," means that Sam gave grapes exclusively to Bill, and not any other person or any other item to Bill. S2 supports this by stating that Bill didn’t get oranges, which aligns with the exclusivity from S1.

S1, with prosodic focus on "BILL," means Sam gave apples exclusively to Bill (and no other person or item to Bill). Given this, S2, which claims Sam didn’t give Bill bananas, is entailed because the focus of S1 rules out any other items being given to Bill.

S1, with prosodic focus on "SUE," means that Sue is the only person who received apples and that she didn’t receive any other fruits. Thus, S2 is entailed as it indicates Sue didn't receive bananas, which is consistent with S1's exclusivity.

S1, with prosodic focus on "ELLEN," means that Ellen is the only recipient of oranges. S2 states that Tom didn’t get any oranges, which is additional and independent information that does not follow directly from S1, but is not in contradiction either.
S1, with prosodic focus on "TOM," means that Tom is the sole recipient of apples. Therefore, S2 is entailed since it aligns with the idea that no one else (like Mary) received apples.
S1, placing focus on "TOM," means Tom is the only person who received apples. S2 contradicts this by stating that Bill also received apples, directly opposing the exclusivity implied by S1.
S1, with prosodic focus on "SUE," means that Sue is the only recipient of bananas. Thus, S2 is entailed as it states that Tom did not receive any bananas, consistent with S1's exclusive focus.
